      <p class="muted">Last Updated: February 2026</p>

      <p>
        These Terms of Use ("Terms") apply to the use of the <strong>HOMU+</strong> app ("the App") provided by Kotaro Omori ("the Developer"). By downloading or using the App, you agree to these Terms.
      </p>

      <h3>1. No Account Required</h3>
      <p>
        The App is designed to work locally on your device without requiring user registration. Your settings, schedules, and usage data are stored on your device or your personal iCloud account (if enabled). The Developer does not manage your user account.
      </p>

      <h3>2. Use of Screen Time API</h3>
      <p>
        The App utilizes Apple's Screen Time API to provide app blocking and focus features.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Functionality:</strong> The App can restrict access to other apps based on the rules you set (schedules, location, or timers).</li>
        <li><strong>Limitation:</strong> Blocking functionality relies entirely on iOS. If you delete the App, all restrictions will be lifted immediately. The Developer is not responsible if the API fails to block apps due to iOS updates or bugs.</li>
        <li><strong>Privacy:</strong> The App cannot access the content of your messages or browsing history through this API.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Location Services</h3>
      <p>
        The App uses location services (geofencing) solely to determine if you are "at home" or "away" for switching focus modes. This processing happens locally on your device.
      </p>

      <h3>4. Premium Features & Subscriptions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Payments:</strong> All transactions are processed by Apple via the App Store.</li>
        <li><strong>Auto-Renewal:</strong> Subscriptions automatically renew unless canceled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.</li>
        <li><strong>Lifetime Purchase:</strong> A one-time purchase grants indefinite access to premium features, subject to the App's lifespan.</li>
        <li><strong>Refunds:</strong> Refunds are handled exclusively by Apple according to their policy. The Developer cannot process refunds directly.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>5. Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>
        The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. The App is a tool to assist with self-control and focus but does not guarantee specific results. The Developer is not liable for any damages (e.g., missed notifications, inability to use other apps during a blocking session) arising from the use of the App.
      </p>

      <h3>6. Changes to Terms</h3>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time. Continued use of the App constitutes acceptance of the new Terms.
